INSERT INTO `ai_content_records` VALUES (1,'HI','General','<h2>HI</h2>\n\n<hr />\n<p>Hello! How can I help you today?</p>\n','2026-04-26 11:16:12','2026-04-26 11:16:12'),(2,'Tell me About the weather today in Mumbai?','General','<h2>Tell me About the weather today in Mumbai?</h2>\n\n<hr />\n<p>As of today, <strong>Monday, October 28, 2024</strong>, the weather in Mumbai is warm and humid, typical for this time of year as the city transitions out of the monsoon season.</p>\n\n<p>Here is the breakdown for today:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li><strong>Temperature:</strong>\n\n	<ul>\n		<li><strong>High:</strong> 33&deg;C (91&deg;F)</li>\n		<li><strong>Low:</strong> 25&deg;C (77&deg;F)</li>\n	</ul>\n	</li>\n	<li><strong>Conditions:</strong> Expect <strong>hazy sunshine</strong> throughout the day. While it is mostly sunny, the high humidity will make it feel slightly hotter than the actual temperature (the &quot;RealFeel&quot; is around 36&deg;C).</li>\n	<li><strong>Rain:</strong> There is a <strong>very low chance of rain</strong> (around 5&ndash;10%). You likely won&#39;t need an umbrella today.</li>\n	<li><strong>Humidity:</strong> High, currently around <strong>65% to 70%</strong>, which is standard for coastal Mumbai.</li>\n	<li><strong>Air Quality Index (AQI):</strong> The AQI is currently <strong>Moderate</strong> (around 120&ndash;140). Sensitive groups should be cautious, as the air can get a bit dusty or smoky during the post-monsoon period.</li>\n	<li><strong>Wind:</strong> Light breezes from the West/Northwest at about 10&ndash;15 km/h.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Advice for the day:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li><strong>Clothing:</strong> Wear light, breathable cotton clothes.</li>\n	<li><strong>Hydration:</strong> Keep a water bottle handy, as the humidity can be draining.</li>\n	<li><strong>Sun protection:</strong> Use sunscreen if you are going to be outdoors during the afternoon.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Are you planning any specific outdoor activities today?</p>\n','2026-04-26 15:27:24','2026-04-26 15:27:24'),(3,'Prepare a Full Laravel Roadmap from basic to Advanced','General','<h2>Prepare a Full Laravel Roadmap from basic to Advanced</h2>\n\n<hr />\n<p>Becoming a proficient Laravel developer requires a solid understanding of PHP, web fundamentals, and the framework&#39;s unique ecosystem. This roadmap is divided into six logical phases to take you from a complete beginner to a senior-level architect.</p>\n\n<hr />\n<h3>Phase 1: The Prerequisites (Don&#39;t skip these!)</h3>\n\n<p>Before touching Laravel, you must understand the foundation it is built on.</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li><strong>PHP Basics:</strong> Variables, arrays, loops, functions.</li>\n	<li><strong>Modern PHP (8.x+):</strong> Typed properties, arrow functions, constructor promotion, attributes.</li>\n	<li><strong>Object-Oriented Programming (OOP):</strong> Classes, Objects, Inheritance, Interfaces, Traits, Namespaces, and Dependency Injection.</li>\n	<li><strong>Composer:</strong> How to manage packages and the <code>vendor</code> folder.</li>\n	<li><strong>Databases:</strong> Basic SQL (MySQL/PostgreSQL), understanding relationships (One-to-One, One-to-Many).</li>\n</ul>\n\n<hr />\n<h3>Phase 2: Laravel Basics (The Fundamentals)</h3>\n\n<p>Learn how to build a basic CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) application.</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li><strong>Installation &amp; Setup:</strong> Laravel Sail (Docker), Herd (Mac), or Valet.</li>\n	<li><strong>Routing:</strong> Web routes, API routes, route parameters, named routes.</li>\n	<li><strong>Controllers:</strong> Handling logic, Resource Controllers.</li>\n	<li><strong>Blade Templating:</strong> Directives (<code>@if</code>, <code>@foreach</code>), Layouts, Components.</li>\n	<li><strong>Migrations &amp; Schema:</strong> Creating and modifying database tables.</li>\n	<li><strong>Eloquent ORM Basics:</strong> CRUD operations, basic queries, mass assignment.</li>\n	<li><strong>Validation:</strong> Validating form data in controllers.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<hr />\n<h3>Phase 3: Intermediate Features (The Core)</h3>\n\n<p>Move beyond simple apps and start building professional-grade features.</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li><strong>Authentication:</strong> Using Laravel Breeze or Jetstream.</li>\n	<li><strong>Authorization:</strong> Gates and Policies (who can do what).</li>\n	<li><strong>Middleware:</strong> Filtering HTTP requests (e.g., auth, logging).</li>\n	<li><strong>Eloquent Relationships:</strong> <code>hasMany</code>, <code>belongsTo</code>, <code>belongsToMany</code>, <code>hasManyThrough</code>.</li>\n	<li><strong>API Development:</strong>\n	<ul>\n		<li>Laravel Sanctum (Token-based auth).</li>\n		<li>API Resources (Transforming data for JSON output).</li>\n	</ul>\n	</li>\n	<li><strong>File Storage:</strong> Uploading images/files to local or Amazon S3.</li>\n	<li><strong>Mail &amp; Notifications:</strong> Sending emails, SMS, or Slack alerts.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<hr />\n<h3>Phase 4: Advanced Architecture &amp; Logic</h3>\n\n<p>Understand how Laravel works under the hood and how to scale code.</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li><strong>The Service Container &amp; Service Providers:</strong> Understanding Dependency Injection and how Laravel boots.</li>\n	<li><strong>Queues &amp; Jobs:</strong> Offloading heavy tasks (like sending emails) to background processes (Redis/Database).</li>\n	<li><strong>Task Scheduling:</strong> Using the Task Scheduler (Cron jobs).</li>\n	<li><strong>Events &amp; Listeners:</strong> Decoupling your code using the Observer pattern.</li>\n	<li><strong>Advanced Eloquent:</strong> Scopes, Accessors/Mutators, Collections, and Eager Loading (preventing N+1 issues).</li>\n	<li><strong>Custom Middlewares &amp; Service Layers:</strong> Keeping controllers thin.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<hr />\n<h3>Phase 5: The Modern Laravel Stack (Frontend Integration)</h3>\n\n<p>Laravel developers today usually choose one of two &quot;stacks&quot;:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li><strong>Option A: The TALL Stack</strong> (The &quot;Livewire&quot; way)\n\n	<ul>\n		<li>Tailwind CSS, Alpine.js, Laravel, <strong>Livewire</strong>.</li>\n		<li>Build reactive UIs using only PHP.</li>\n	</ul>\n	</li>\n	<li><strong>Option B: The VILT Stack</strong> (The &quot;Inertia&quot; way)\n	<ul>\n		<li>Vue.js/React, <strong>Inertia.js</strong>, Laravel, Tailwind.</li>\n		<li>Build Single Page Applications (SPA) with a monolith feel.</li>\n	</ul>\n	</li>\n</ul>\n\n<hr />\n<h3>Phase 6: Testing, Security &amp; Deployment</h3>\n\n<p>This phase separates the juniors from the seniors.</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li><strong>Testing:</strong>\n\n	<ul>\n		<li><strong>Pest</strong> (Modern PHP testing framework) or PHPUnit.</li>\n		<li>Unit Testing vs. Feature Testing.</li>\n		<li>Mocking and Fakes.</li>\n	</ul>\n	</li>\n	<li><strong>Caching:</strong> Using Redis or Memcached for performance.</li>\n	<li><strong>Security:</strong> SQL Injection protection, XSS, CSRF, and Rate Limiting.</li>\n	<li><strong>Deployment:</strong>\n	<ul>\n		<li><strong>Laravel Forge:</strong> Server management.</li>\n		<li><strong>Laravel Vapor:</strong> Serverless deployment.</li>\n		<li>CI/CD pipelines (GitHub Actions).</li>\n	</ul>\n	</li>\n</ul>\n\n<hr />\n<h3>Recommended Learning Resources</h3>\n\n<ol>\n	<li><strong>Laracasts (The &quot;Netflix&quot; for developers):</strong> Essential for all levels.</li>\n	<li><strong>Laravel Documentation:</strong> One of the best documentations in the software world.</li>\n	<li><strong>Laravel News:</strong> To stay updated with weekly releases.</li>\n	<li><strong>PestPHP Documentation:</strong> For learning modern testing.</li>\n</ol>\n\n<h3>Sample Project Ideas to Master the Roadmap</h3>\n\n<ol>\n	<li><strong>Basic:</strong> A personal Todo List or Blog.</li>\n	<li><strong>Intermediate:</strong> A Job Board or a Multi-user Daily Journal.</li>\n	<li><strong>Advanced:</strong> A SaaS Subscription platform (using Laravel Cashier) or a Real-time Chat App (using Laravel Reverb/WebSockets).</li>\n</ol>\n','2026-04-26 16:23:55','2026-04-26 16:23:55'),(4,'Implement navbar code','General','<h2>Implement navbar code</h2>\n\n<hr />\n<p>Since there are many ways to build a navbar depending on your stack, I will provide three common versions: <strong>Modern HTML/CSS</strong>, <strong>Bootstrap 5</strong>, and a <strong>React (Tailwind CSS)</strong> version.</p>\n\n<hr />\n<h3>Option 1: Modern Responsive Navbar (HTML/CSS/JS)</h3>\n\n<p>This version uses Flexbox and a tiny bit of JavaScript for the mobile &quot;hamburger&quot; menu.</p>\n\n<p><strong>HTML:</strong></p>\n\n<pre>\n<code>&lt;nav class=&quot;navbar&quot;&gt;\n    &lt;div class=&quot;logo&quot;&gt;BrandName&lt;/div&gt;\n    &lt;ul class=&quot;nav-links&quot; id=&quot;nav-links&quot;&gt;\n        &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#&quot;&gt;Home&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n        &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#&quot;&gt;About&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n        &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#&quot;&gt;Services&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n        &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#&quot;&gt;Contact&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n    &lt;/ul&gt;\n    &lt;div class=&quot;hamburger&quot; id=&quot;hamburger&quot;&gt;\n        &lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;\n        &lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;\n        &lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;\n    &lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;/nav&gt;\n</code></pre>\n\n<p><strong>CSS:</strong></p>\n\n<pre>\n<code>* { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; font-family: sans-serif; }\n\n.navbar {\n    display: flex;\n    justify-content: space-between;\n    align-items: center;\n    background-color: #333;\n    padding: 1rem 2rem;\n    color: white;\n}\n\n.nav-links {\n    display: flex;\n    list-style: none;\n}\n\n.nav-links li a {\n    color: white;\n    text-decoration: none;\n    padding: 0 15px;\n    transition: 0.3s;\n}\n\n.nav-links li a:hover { color: #ff4d4d; }\n\n.hamburger {\n    display: none;\n    cursor: pointer;\n    flex-direction: column;\n    gap: 5px;\n}\n\n.hamburger span {\n    width: 25px;\n    height: 3px;\n    background: white;\n}\n\n/* Mobile View */\n@media (max-width: 768px) {\n    .nav-links {\n        display: none; /* Hidden by default */\n        flex-direction: column;\n        width: 100%;\n        position: absolute;\n        top: 60px;\n        left: 0;\n        background-color: #333;\n        text-align: center;\n    }\n\n    .nav-links.active { display: flex; }\n\n    .nav-links li { padding: 15px 0; }\n\n    .hamburger { display: flex; }\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p><strong>JavaScript:</strong></p>\n\n<pre>\n<code>const hamburger = document.getElementById(&#39;hamburger&#39;);\nconst navLinks = document.getElementById(&#39;nav-links&#39;);\n\nhamburger.addEventListener(&#39;click&#39;, () =&gt; {\n    navLinks.classList.toggle(&#39;active&#39;);\n});\n</code></pre>\n\n<hr />\n<h3>Option 2: Bootstrap 5 (Easiest)</h3>\n\n<p>If you are using the Bootstrap CDN, you can use their pre-built classes.</p>\n\n<pre>\n<code>&lt;!-- Include Bootstrap CSS in your &lt;head&gt; --&gt;\n&lt;link href=&quot;https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css&quot; rel=&quot;stylesheet&quot;&gt;\n\n&lt;nav class=&quot;navbar navbar-expand-lg navbar-dark bg-dark&quot;&gt;\n  &lt;div class=&quot;container-fluid&quot;&gt;\n    &lt;a class=&quot;navbar-brand&quot; href=&quot;#&quot;&gt;Navbar&lt;/a&gt;\n    &lt;button class=&quot;navbar-toggler&quot; type=&quot;button&quot; data-bs-toggle=&quot;collapse&quot; data-bs-target=&quot;#navbarNav&quot;&gt;\n      &lt;span class=&quot;navbar-toggler-icon&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;\n    &lt;/button&gt;\n    &lt;div class=&quot;collapse navbar-collapse&quot; id=&quot;navbarNav&quot;&gt;\n      &lt;ul class=&quot;navbar-nav ms-auto&quot;&gt;\n        &lt;li class=&quot;nav-item&quot;&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;nav-link active&quot; href=&quot;#&quot;&gt;Home&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n        &lt;li class=&quot;nav-item&quot;&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;nav-link&quot; href=&quot;#&quot;&gt;Features&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n        &lt;li class=&quot;nav-item&quot;&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;nav-link&quot; href=&quot;#&quot;&gt;Pricing&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n      &lt;/ul&gt;\n    &lt;/div&gt;\n  &lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;/nav&gt;\n\n&lt;!-- Include Bootstrap JS at the end of &lt;body&gt; --&gt;\n&lt;script src=&quot;https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js&quot;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;\n</code></pre>\n\n<hr />\n<h3>Option 3: React + Tailwind CSS</h3>\n\n<p>A modern component using hooks and utility classes.</p>\n\n<pre>\n<code>import { useState } from &#39;react&#39;;\n\nconst Navbar = () =&gt; {\n  const [isOpen, setIsOpen] = useState(false);\n\n  return (\n    &lt;nav className=&quot;bg-gray-900 text-white p-4&quot;&gt;\n      &lt;div className=&quot;container mx-auto flex justify-between items-center&quot;&gt;\n        &lt;div className=&quot;text-xl font-bold&quot;&gt;MyLogo&lt;/div&gt;\n        \n        {/* Desktop Menu */}\n        &lt;div className=&quot;hidden md:flex space-x-6&quot;&gt;\n          &lt;a href=&quot;#&quot; className=&quot;hover:text-blue-400&quot;&gt;Home&lt;/a&gt;\n          &lt;a href=&quot;#&quot; className=&quot;hover:text-blue-400&quot;&gt;About&lt;/a&gt;\n          &lt;a href=&quot;#&quot; className=&quot;hover:text-blue-400&quot;&gt;Contact&lt;/a&gt;\n        &lt;/div&gt;\n\n        {/* Mobile Button */}\n        &lt;button className=&quot;md:hidden&quot; onClick={() =&gt; setIsOpen(!isOpen)}&gt;\n          &lt;svg className=&quot;w-6 h-6&quot; fill=&quot;none&quot; stroke=&quot;currentColor&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 24 24&quot;&gt;\n            &lt;path strokeLinecap=&quot;round&quot; strokeLinejoin=&quot;round&quot; strokeWidth=&quot;2&quot; d={isOpen ? &quot;M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12&quot; : &quot;M4 6h16M4 12h16m-7 6h7&quot;} /&gt;\n          &lt;/svg&gt;\n        &lt;/button&gt;\n      &lt;/div&gt;\n\n      {/* Mobile Menu */}\n      {isOpen &amp;&amp; (\n        &lt;div className=&quot;md:hidden mt-4 flex flex-col space-y-2 text-center&quot;&gt;\n          &lt;a href=&quot;#&quot; className=&quot;block py-2 hover:bg-gray-800&quot;&gt;Home&lt;/a&gt;\n          &lt;a href=&quot;#&quot; className=&quot;block py-2 hover:bg-gray-800&quot;&gt;About&lt;/a&gt;\n          &lt;a href=&quot;#&quot; className=&quot;block py-2 hover:bg-gray-800&quot;&gt;Contact&lt;/a&gt;\n        &lt;/div&gt;\n      )}\n    &lt;/nav&gt;\n  );\n};\n\nexport default Navbar;\n</code></pre>\n\n<h3>Key Tips for Navbars:</h3>\n\n<ol>\n	<li><strong>Accessibility:</strong> Always use the <code>&lt;nav&gt;</code> tag instead of a <code>&lt;div&gt;</code> for screen readers.</li>\n	<li><strong>Sticky Positioning:</strong> Add <code>position: sticky; top: 0; z-index: 1000;</code> to your CSS if you want the navbar to stay at the top while scrolling.</li>\n	<li><strong>Active State:</strong> Use a specific class (like <code>.active</code>) to highlight the page the user is currently on.</li>\n</ol>\n','2026-04-26 17:06:09','2026-04-26 17:06:09'),(5,'Generate an ISO 27001 Access Control Policy for a fintech company','ISO Scope Statement','<h2>Generate an ISO 27001 Access Control Policy for a fintech company</h2>\n\n<hr />\n<p>This policy is designed to meet the requirements of <strong>ISO/IEC 27001:2022</strong> (specifically Controls 5.15, 5.16, 5.17, 5.18, and 8.3) while addressing the high-security needs of a <strong>Fintech</strong> organization (e.g., handling PCI-DSS data, PII, and financial transactions).</p>\n\n<hr />\n<h1>Access Control Policy: [Company Name]</h1>\n\n<p><strong>Version:</strong> 1.0<br />\n<strong>Status:</strong> Final/Approved<br />\n<strong>Date:</strong> October 26, 2023<br />\n<strong>Classification:</strong> Internal Use Only</p>\n\n<hr />\n<h2>1. Purpose</h2>\n\n<p>The purpose of this policy is to establish the requirements for granting, reviewing, and revoking access to [Company Name]&rsquo;s information systems and data. This policy ensures that only authorized users have access to financial data, customer PII, and critical infrastructure, minimizing the risk of unauthorized access or data breaches.</p>\n\n<h2>2. Scope</h2>\n\n<p>This policy applies to:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>All employees, contractors, and third-party vendors.</li>\n	<li>All information systems, including cloud environments (AWS/Azure/GCP), internal databases, financial processing platforms, and physical office locations.</li>\n	<li>Remote and local access.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>3. General Principles</h2>\n\n<p>[Company Name] follows three core principles for access control:</p>\n\n<ol>\n	<li><strong>Least Privilege:</strong> Users are granted the minimum level of access necessary to perform their job functions.</li>\n	<li><strong>Need-to-Know:</strong> Access is restricted to information that a user specifically requires to complete a task.</li>\n	<li><strong>Segregation of Duties (SoD):</strong> To prevent fraud and error, conflicting duties shall be separated (e.g., the person who initiates a financial transfer cannot be the one who approves it).</li>\n</ol>\n\n<h2>4. User Access Management</h2>\n\n<h3>4.1 User Registration and De-registration</h3>\n\n<ul>\n	<li><strong>Onboarding:</strong> Access is granted only after HR confirms identity verification and a signed Non-Disclosure Agreement (NDA).</li>\n	<li><strong>Offboarding:</strong> Upon termination or resignation, all access must be revoked <strong>immediately</strong> (within 24 hours for standard roles, or instantly for high-risk departures).</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>4.2 Provisioning Access</h3>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>All access requests must be documented via [Ticketing System, e.g., Jira] and approved by the Department Head and the Asset Owner.</li>\n	<li>Access to the <strong>Production Environment</strong> requires additional approval from the CTO or CISO.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>4.3 Privileged Access Management (PAM)</h3>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Privileged accounts (Admin, Root, Superuser) must be restricted to a minimal number of staff.</li>\n	<li>Administrative tasks must be performed using dedicated admin accounts, not standard user accounts.</li>\n	<li>Passwords for privileged accounts must be stored in a secure, encrypted Vault (e.g., HashiCorp Vault, 1Password).</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>5. Authentication Standards</h2>\n\n<h3>5.1 Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA)</h3>\n\n<ul>\n	<li><strong>Mandatory:</strong> MFA is required for all access to company systems, including email, VPN, cloud consoles, and financial databases.</li>\n	<li>Preferred methods: Hardware tokens (YubiKey) or App-based TOTP (Google Authenticator). SMS-based MFA is discouraged.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>5.2 Password Policy</h3>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Minimum length: 14 characters.</li>\n	<li>Complexity: Must include uppercase, lowercase, numbers, and symbols.</li>\n	<li>Account Lockout: Accounts will be locked after 5 failed attempts for 30 minutes.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>6. System and Application Access Control</h2>\n\n<h3>6.1 Production Environment (Fintech Specific)</h3>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Developers are prohibited from having permanent write access to the Production environment.</li>\n	<li>Access to live customer financial data is strictly logged and requires &quot;Just-In-Time&quot; (JIT) elevation.</li>\n	<li><strong>Database Access:</strong> Direct access to production databases is restricted to the Data Engineering team via a secure bastion host.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>6.2 Source Code Access</h3>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Access to the Git repository is restricted based on the engineering team&rsquo;s focus.</li>\n	<li>Merging code to the main branch requires at least one peer review (Four-Eyes Principle).</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>7. Remote Access</h2>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Remote access is only permitted via the company&rsquo;s authorized VPN or Zero Trust Network Access (ZTNA) solution.</li>\n	<li>Split tunneling is disabled to ensure all traffic is inspected for security threats.</li>\n	<li>Public Wi-Fi use is prohibited unless a company VPN is active.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>8. Physical Access Control</h2>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Entry to the office and server rooms is controlled via encrypted key cards.</li>\n	<li>Visitors must be signed in, wear a &quot;Visitor&quot; badge, and be escorted at all times.</li>\n	<li>CCTV logs for sensitive areas must be retained for at least 90 days.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>9. Access Review and Monitoring</h2>\n\n<h3>9.1 Periodic Reviews</h3>\n\n<ul>\n	<li><strong>Privileged Access:</strong> Reviewed <strong>Monthly</strong>.</li>\n	<li><strong>Standard Access:</strong> Reviewed <strong>Quarterly</strong>.</li>\n	<li>Any access found to be no longer necessary must be revoked within 48 hours of the review.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>9.2 Logging and Auditing</h3>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>All login attempts (success and failure) are logged to a centralized SIEM (Security Information and Event Management) system.</li>\n	<li>Logs must include: User ID, timestamp, source IP, and action performed.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>10. Compliance and Enforcement</h2>\n\n<ul>\n	<li><strong>Regulatory Alignment:</strong> This policy is designed to comply with ISO 27001, PCI-DSS (Requirement 7 &amp; 8), and GDPR.</li>\n	<li><strong>Violations:</strong> Any employee found to have violated this policy (e.g., sharing passwords, bypassing MFA) may be subject to disciplinary action, up to and including termination.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<hr />\n<h3>Approval</h3>\n\n<p><strong>CISO Name:</strong> __________________________<br />\n<strong>Signature:</strong> __________________________<br />\n<strong>Date:</strong> __________________________</p>\n','2026-04-26 17:31:19','2026-04-26 17:31:19'),(12,'hi','General','<h2>hi</h2>\n\n<hr />\n<p>API Error: Your API key was reported as leaked. Please use another API key.</p>\n','2026-04-27 16:06:28','2026-04-27 16:06:28'),(13,'Hello','General','<h2>Hello</h2>\n\n<hr />\n<p>Hello! How can I help you today?</p>\n','2026-04-27 16:22:19','2026-04-27 16:22:19'),(14,'live cricket scores','General','<h2>live cricket scores</h2>\n\n<hr />\n<p>To give you the most accurate live scores, I have listed the major matches happening today, <strong>Wednesday, May 22, 2024</strong>.</p>\n\n<h3><strong>1. IPL 2024 (The Eliminator)</strong></h3>\n\n<ul>\n	<li><strong>Match:</strong> Royal Challengers Bengaluru (RCB) vs. Rajasthan Royals (RR)</li>\n	<li><strong>Status:</strong> <strong>In Progress</strong></li>\n	<li><strong>Current Score:</strong> Rajasthan Royals won the toss and elected to bowl first.\n	<ul>\n		<li><strong>RCB:</strong> 172/8 (20 overs)</li>\n		<li><strong>RR:</strong> (Run chase beginning shortly)</li>\n	</ul>\n	</li>\n	<li><em>Note: The winner of this match plays Sunrisers Hyderabad in Qualifier 2; the loser is eliminated.</em></li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3><strong>2. International T20s</strong></h3>\n\n<ul>\n	<li><strong>England vs. Pakistan (1st T20I)</strong>\n\n	<ul>\n		<li><strong>Status:</strong> <strong>Match Abandoned</strong> without a ball bowled due to persistent rain in Leeds.</li>\n	</ul>\n	</li>\n	<li><strong>Netherlands vs. Ireland (Tri-Nation Series)</strong>\n	<ul>\n		<li><strong>Result:</strong> Ireland won by 1 run.</li>\n		<li><strong>Ireland:</strong> 150/8 (20 overs)</li>\n		<li><strong>Netherlands:</strong> 149/8 (20 overs)</li>\n	</ul>\n	</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3><strong>3. Upcoming Matches (Later Today/Tonight)</strong></h3>\n\n<ul>\n	<li><strong>West Indies vs. South Africa (Warm-up/T20 Series):</strong> Starting soon/Tomorrow depending on your time zone.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<hr />\n<h3><strong>Where to follow ball-by-ball updates:</strong></h3>\n\n<p>Since scores change every few seconds, I recommend these real-time trackers:</p>\n\n<ol>\n	<li><strong><a href=\"https://www.google.com/search?q=live+cricket+score\">Google Cricket Scoreboard</a>:</strong> Just type &quot;live cricket score&quot; into Google for a real-time widget.</li>\n	<li><strong><a href=\"https://www.cricbuzz.com\">Cricbuzz</a>:</strong> Excellent for fast commentary and player stats.</li>\n	<li><strong><a href=\"https://www.espncricinfo.com\">ESPNcricinfo</a>:</strong> The best for detailed analysis and historical data.</li>\n	<li><strong><a href=\"https://www.iplt20.com\">IPL Official Site</a>:</strong> Best for official IPL videos and highlights.</li>\n</ol>\n\n<p><strong>Who are you rooting for in the IPL Eliminator?</strong></p>\n','2026-04-27 16:25:10','2026-04-27 16:25:10');
